name: Anderson's Meadow Orchard
short_description: Community fruit trees by the Wensum.
description: A riverside meadow featuring community-planted apple and pear trees open for public picking.

name: Mousehold Heath Hazelnuts
description: Hazel and sweet chestnut trees are scattered throughout this historic 184-acre woodland.

name: River Wensum Wild Garlic
description: Find wild garlic in the shaded, damp areas along the Wensum riverside path near Pull's Ferry.

name: Grapes Hill Community Garden
description: A former piece of wasteland now overflowing with fruit trees, herbs, and soft fruit for the public.

name: Marriott's Way Blackberries
description: The old railway line is a corridor of blackberries and elderberries stretching for miles.

name: Incredible Edible NR3
description: Raised beds on Silver Road and nearby streets featuring kale, chard, and kitchen herbs.

name: Earlham Park Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees can be found near the edges of the parkland close to the UEA campus.

name: Whitlingham Broad Sea Buckthorn
description: While usually coastal, Sea Buckthorn can be found in the scrubby areas of this country park.

name: The Great Hospital Plums
description: Plum and greengage trees overhang public paths in the historic cathedral quarter.

name: Eaton Park Sloes
description: Large crops of sloes can be gathered from the park's perimeter hedgerows.

name: UEA Edible Campus Planters
description: Raised beds across campus featuring salad leaves, herbs, and strawberries for public picking.

name: Brundall Marina Sea Samphire
description: Marsh samphire and sea aster found on the tidal muddy banks of the Yare (coastal-style foraging).

name: Heigham Park Rosehips
short_description: Wild roses in the Golden Triangle.
description: Abundant wild rosehips in the shrubbery borders of this classic urban park.

name: Waterloo Park Orchard
short_description: Apple trees in a Grade II park.
description: A small collection of apple trees available for public use near the pavilion.

name: Marston Marsh Wild Celery
description: Wild celery and watermint found along the damp dykes of the marshland.
